      "question": "What is RAG and how does it work?",
      "answer": "RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation. It is a technique used in AI systems to improve the accuracy and relevance of generated responses by combining information retrieved from a database with the model's own knowledge. The process typically involves retrieving relevant documents or chunks of information from a database, then using those retrieved pieces of information to inform the generation of a response by the AI model."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the difference between Naïve RAG and Advanced RAG?",
      "answer": "Naïve RAG is a simplified version of the RAG approach that provides decent results but lacks the complexity required for accurate, reliable, and verifiable answers. Advanced RAG, on the other hand, includes additional pre- and post-processing steps to enhance the quality of the results. These steps may include query rewriting, re-ranking retrieved documents, filtering irrelevant information, and ensuring that the generated answers meet quality and safety standards."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is a 'golden dataset' and why is it important?",
      "answer": "A 'golden dataset' is a carefully curated and annotated dataset used as a benchmark for evaluating the performance of AI models. It is important because it allows teams to test and measure the impact of changes in the system, such as updates to the knowledge base or changes in the retrieval and generation processes. It helps ensure that the AI-generated results are accurate, reliable, and meet the required quality standards."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the role of the Knowledge Service in the Q&A Assist system?",
      "answer": "The Knowledge Service is responsible for breaking down Microsoft Learn's technical documentation into chunks, creating embedding vectors for each chunk, and storing these vectors and chunks in a database. This is a crucial part of the data engineering effort, as it ensures that the system can efficiently retrieve and use the most relevant information when generating responses."
