        "description": "Machine learning is used in the form of multi-class logistic regression with L2 penalty for merchant classification. The model uses features such as identified merchant names (encoded using InferSent embeddings) and MCC codes (one-hot encoded). The model is retrained monthly to adapt to data shifts."
      },
      "deep_learning": {
        "used": true,
        "description": "Deep learning is used via the InferSent model, a pre-trained sentence embedding model developed by Facebook, to encode merchant names. This model captures semantic meaning and sequence information in text, improving the accuracy of the classification task."
      },
      "natural_language_processing": {
        "used": true,
        "description": "NLP techniques are used for preprocessing merchant names, including the use of count vectorizers and sentence embeddings (InferSent) to encode text data."
      },
