{
  "summary": "This document outlines Shopify's comprehensive approach to building and deploying a multimodal large language model (LLM) system for product understanding, entity resolution, and canonical representation of products. The system is designed to handle the vast and dynamic nature of e-commerce data, with a focus on scalability, accuracy, and cost-effectiveness. The architecture consists of four key layers: product data foundation, product understanding, product matching, and reconciliation. Each layer leverages multimodal LLMs to extract and normalize product metadata, identify duplicate listings, and create a unified product record. The system also includes advanced techniques for model fine-tuning, data generation, and continuous improvement through active learning. The deployment infrastructure is optimized for high throughput and low latency, supporting 40 million LLM calls daily. The impact of the system is already being felt across Shopify's ecosystem, improving data quality, search relevance, and recommendation accuracy.",
  "key_points": {
    "architecture": {
      "layers": [
        "Product data foundation: Handles the full variety, volume, and volatility of commerce data.",
        "Product understanding: Transforms unstructured data into standardized metadata through multiple tasks such as classification, attribute extraction, and image understanding.",
        "Product matching: Identifies when different merchants sell the same item using a multi-stage process involving candidate generation and discriminators.",
        "Reconciliation: Constructs a canonical product record by aggregating all inferred metadata."
      ]
    },
    "model_training": {
      "fine_tuning": {
        "models": ["LlaVA 1.5 7B", "LLaMA 3.2 11B", "Qwen2VL 7B"],
        "approach": "Selective field extraction during training to improve generalization and reduce latency."
      },
      "data_generation": {
        "pipeline": "Combines LLM agents and human expertise for annotation.",
        "metrics": [
          "Task-specific metrics: Precision/recall for classification, accuracy for attribute extraction.",
          "LLM judge metrics: Synthetic judges grade outputs against detailed guidelines.",
          "Instruction metrics: Measure instruction following capability."
        ]
      }
    },
    "deployment_infrastructure": {
      "optimizations": [
        "Triton inference server: Orchestrates model serving across GPU fleet.",
        "FP8 quantization: Reduces GPU memory footprint while maintaining inference accuracy.",
        "Selective field prompting: Reduces latency and GPU token usage."
      ],
      "throughput": "Supports 40 million LLM calls daily, representing about 16 billion tokens inferred per day."
    },
    "impact": {
      "merchant_admin": "Provides real-time suggestions on category classification and missing attributes during product creation.",
      "search_and_recommendations": "Enriched product data and universal identifiers enable better matching, faceting, and surfacing of relevant results.",
      "embeddings_creation": "Product and variant representations inform core ML functionality for personalized ranking and recommendations."
    }
  },
  "conclusion": "Shopify's multimodal LLM system represents a significant advancement in e-commerce data processing, enabling more accurate product understanding, efficient entity resolution, and robust canonical representation. The system's scalability, accuracy, and cost-effectiveness make it a powerful tool for improving data quality, search relevance, and recommendation accuracy across Shopify's ecosystem."
}

