{
  "ai_analysis": {
    "summary": "The article details the implementation and success of Hybrid Search at OLX, combining keyword-based retrieval with vector search using semantic similarity. The approach was tested in a low-risk market before a full rollout, and it showed significant improvements in user engagement, including a 3% increase in successful events on apps and a 5% increase on mobile web. The solution involved using E5 models for semantic search, integrating results with keyword-based retrieval, and retraining the Learning to Rank (LTR) model to account for vector similarity scores. The success of the experiment has led to plans for a full rollout across all markets.",
    "key_points": [
      "Hybrid Search combines keyword-based retrieval with vector search using semantic similarity.",
      "E5 models were used for semantic search due to their lightweight inference and support for longer inputs.",
      "A fixed-size allocation approach was used to combine results from both retrieval methods.",
      "The LTR model was retrained to include vector similarity scores as a feature.",
      "Initial experiments showed a more than 100% increase in successful events per user.",
      "A/B testing confirmed the effectiveness of Hybrid Search, with improvements in user engagement and search efficiency.",
      "The solution was rolled out across all platforms in the tested market, with plans to expand to other markets."
    ],
    "conclusion": "The implementation of Hybrid Search at OLX has demonstrated significant improvements in search relevance and user engagement. The combination of keyword-based and semantic search, along with the retraining of the LTR model, has proven to be a successful approach. The next step is to expand this solution to all markets, starting with the largest ones."
  }
}

