    "summary": "The article discusses the implementation of personalized search ranking at Etsy, leveraging user interaction data and advanced machine learning techniques to improve the relevance of search results. The system uses a combination of user behavior (clicks, favorites, add-to-cart, purchases), textual analysis (Tf-Idf), and graph-based embeddings (interaction-based and item-interaction) to create rich user contextual vectors. These vectors are then used in a decision tree model to rank items, resulting in improved user engagement and purchase rates. The article also highlights challenges such as increased latency due to personalization and considerations around privacy and user preferences.",
    "key_points": [
      "Etsy uses a combination of user behavior, textual analysis, and graph-based embeddings to create user contextual vectors for personalized search ranking.",
